    "The user requests the agent to fix a bug on their website.",
    "To fulfill this request, the agent reads a (contaminated) GitHub issue containing an indirect prompt injection (in red) and a foot-in-the-door distractor (in blue).",
    "These injected requests infiltrate the agent's thought process (step 4), leading it to proceed with them.",
    "This intrusion ultimately drives the agent to execute both the attacker's harmless distractor request (calculate 2+4) and the attacker's malicious instruction (send Admin Credentials to the attacker).",
    "FITD attack significantly increases the attack success rate (ASR) across all tested models."
  ],
